14 Section 1. Section 61-9-226, MCA, is amended to read:
15 "61-9-226. Special restrictions on lamps -- definition. (1) A lighted lamp or illuminating device upon
16 a motor vehicle other than headlamps, spot lamps, auxiliary lamps, or flashing turn signals, emergency vehicle
17 warning lamps, and school bus warning lamps that projects a beam of light of an intensity greater than 300
18 candlepower must be so directed that the high intensity portion of the beam may not strike the level of the
19 roadway on which the vehicle stands at a distance of more than 75 feet from the vehicle.
20 (2) A person may not drive or move a vehicle or equipment upon a highway with:
21 (a) a lamp or device displaying a red light visible from in front of the center of the vehicle. This
22 section does not apply to a vehicle upon which a red light visible from the front is expressly authorized or
23 required by this code.
24 (b) green lights that are flashing, rotational, or continuous, except for vehicles that are authorized
25 by this chapter to contain the lights, including:
26 (i) snow-removal equipment operated by the department of transportation or another government
27 entity; and
28 (ii) a police or authorized emergency vehicle that is an on-scene incident command or control
